data.database_description: This database manages customer interactions and transactions, encompassing various entities such as customers, products, premises for delivery addresses, mailshot campaigns for marketing purposes, and order details including shipping information and item statuses. The tables are interconnected through foreign key relationships, facilitating comprehensive tracking of customer orders, product categorization, and the effectiveness of marketing campaigns.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each premise.
Type of the premise, such as Warehouse, Residence, or Office.
Detailed description or address of the premise.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about various premises used for delivery addresses.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each product.
Category under which the product is classified.
Name of the product.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about products available for purchase, including their category and name.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each customer.
Payment method used by the customer (e.g., Credit Card, Direct Debit).
Name of the customer.
Phone number of the customer.
Email address of the customer.
Shipping address of the customer.
Login username for the customer's account.
Password for the customer's account.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about customers including their contact details, payment methods, and login credentials.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each mailshot campaign.
Category of products targeted in the mailshot campaign.
Name or title of the mailshot campaign.
Start date and time of the mailshot campaign.
End date and time of the mailshot campaign.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about mailshot campaigns, including details such as campaign ID, product category, name, and date range.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the customer.
Identifier linking to the address details stored in the Premises table.
Start date of the address validity period.
Type of address, such as Billing or Shipping.
End date of the address validity period.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about customer addresses, including type and validity period.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each order.
Identifier linking the order to a specific customer.
Current status of the order, such as 'Cancelled', 'Delivered', or 'Paid'.
Code representing the method used for shipping the order, e.g., 'FedEx' or 'UPS'.
Date and time when the order was placed.
Date and time when the order was delivered.
Charges associated with shipping the order, represented as a string value.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about customer orders, including order status, shipping details, and timestamps.

columns.columnDescription: Reference to the mailshot campaign ID from the Mailshot_Campaigns table.
Unique identifier for each customer, linking to the Customers table.
Result of the interaction between the mailshot and the customer (e.g., Order, No Response).
Date and time when the interaction occurred.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records the interaction between customers and mailshot campaigns, including outcome codes and timestamps.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each item in an order.
Status code indicating the current state of the item in the order.
Identifier linking the item to its parent order.
Identifier linking the item to its associated product.
Status code indicating the condition or quality of the item.
Date and time when the item was delivered to the customer.
Quantity of the product ordered for this item.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about items within customer orders, including their status and delivery information.
